Date: Tue, 3 Mar 2026 22:30:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 18/18] fix(config): remove sessionPolicies from config schema,
 hardcode defaults

OpenClaw 2026.3.2 removed sessionPolicies from the config schema,
causing "Unrecognized key" validation errors. This patch:

1. Removes sessionPolicies from zod-schema.ts (no longer registered)
2. Removes sessionPolicies from types.openclaw.ts (no longer typed)
3. Removes sessionPolicies UI hints from schema.ts
4. Hardcodes default policy values in pi-tools.ts instead of reading
   from config

The exec guard logic in bash-tools.exec.ts is unchanged — it still
uses the ExecMainSessionPolicy type and enforces the policy, but now
the values come from hardcoded defaults rather than config.
---
 src/agents/pi-tools.ts        | 12 ++++++++++--
 src/config/types.openclaw.ts  | 11 -----------
 src/config/zod-schema.ts      | 20 --------------------
 src/config/schema.ts          | 18 ------------------
 4 files changed, 10 insertions(+), 51 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/agents/pi-tools.ts b/src/agents/pi-tools.ts
index 9d11100..a1b2c3d 100644
--- a/src/agents/pi-tools.ts
+++ b/src/agents/pi-tools.ts
@@ -147,8 +147,16 @@ function resolveExecConfig(params: { cfg?: OpenClawConfig; agentId?: string }) {
       agentExec?.notifyOnExitEmptySuccess ?? globalExec?.notifyOnExitEmptySuccess,
     applyPatch: agentExec?.applyPatch ?? globalExec?.applyPatch,
-    mainSessionPolicy: cfg?.sessionPolicies?.main,
-    sessionPolicies: cfg?.sessionPolicies,
+    mainSessionPolicy: {
+      forbidLongExec: true,
+      requireBackgroundForExec: true,
+      maxExecTimeoutSec: 120,
+      maxOutputBytes: 102400,
+    },
+    sessionPolicies: {
+      main: { forbidLongExec: true, requireBackgroundForExec: true, maxExecTimeoutSec: 120, maxOutputBytes: 102400 },
+      subagent: { maxOutputBytes: 0 },
+    },
   };
 }
 
